data.question: What is ComfyUI-Prompt-Preview?
data.answer: ComfyUI-Prompt-Preview is a tool that allows users to visualize the styles from the SDXL Prompt Styler.

data.question: What does ComfyUI-Prompt-Preview showcase?
data.answer: ComfyUI-Prompt-Preview showcases the capabilities of the SDXL Prompt Styler with preview images.

data.question: How can I see how my prompts could appear with the various styles available?
data.answer: You can view how your prompts could appear with the various styles by looking at the preview images provided in the ComfyUI-Prompt-Preview repository.

data.question: What images are included in the repository?
data.answer: The repository includes preview images from the SDXL Prompt Styler and the SDXL Prompt Styler Advanced.

data.question: Where can I find more information about the SDXL Prompt Styler?
data.answer: For more information about the SDXL Prompt Styler, you can visit the [sdxl_prompt_styler](https://github.com/twri/sdxl_prompt_styler).

data.question: Is there a repository that contains custom scripts for ComfyUI?
data.answer: Yes, you can find custom scripts for ComfyUI in the [ComfyUI-Custom-Scripts](https://github.com/pythongosssss/ComfyUI-Custom-Scripts).

data.question: What version of sdxl was used to generate the preview images?
data.answer: The preview images in the project were generated using sdxl version 1.0.
